    • resolve

      <T> T resolve(T base, BiFunction<? super ModelElement,T,T> resolver, ConnectionBase connectionBase)
      Resolves some value for the model element by traversing its logical containment hierarchy and resolving that value against logical parents. For the containment root the value is resolved against the base.
      Type Parameters:
      T -
      Parameters:
      base - Base value is used to resolve the parent value
      resolver - Resolver BiFunction
      connectionBase - Indicates logical "mounting" of connections.
      Returns:
